{
  "text": "The ~ receptors appear to play a role in locomotion, because both naltrindole and a benzofuran derivative of it, naltriben, blocked morphine-induced hyperactivity [CITATION_1] . Naltrindole also reduced the gross motor stimulation of amphetamine but not of cocaine. Because the 61 antagonist DALCE had no effect and because the 62 antagonist naltrindole-5'-isothiocynate or a combination of it and DALCE reduced the behavior induced by amphetamine in a manner similar to that of naltrindole, it was concluded that both subtypes of/~ receptors might have a role in amphetamine behavioral activation [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "20592062",
